Syntax
    configure.sh takes the following options

    # Public Network
    -P NIC 
	Public network interface (default guessed from default route), e.g. eth0
    -F cidr
	Floating (Public) IP range e.g. 172.16.1.0/24
	e.g. "-F 172.16.1.0/24"  creates 172.16.1.0-255 as addresses to use

    # Private Network
    -p NIC
	Private network interface that gets the VLANs assignedi, e.g. eth1
    -f cidr
	Fixed (Private) IP range e.g. 10.0.0.0/8
    -s num (default 256)
	Network size (IP address range on this network)
    -n num (default 1)
	Number of VLAN networks to create (default 1)
    -V num
	VLAN Tag ID Start (default 100)

    -C address 	
	Cloud Controller Address (default is worked out from public interface IP)
	Note: Required if specifying "compute" installation option
    -v { qemu | kvm }
	Virtualization type: qemu for software, kvm for kvm (hardware)
	Worked out automatically if omitted
    -M address  
	MySQL IP (default Cloud Controller address)

    -h: Produces this help
